   "source": [
    "# Agentic ETL Reverse Engineering & Data Vault Pipeline\n",
    "**Input:** DataStage (.dsx/.xml) | Informatica (.xml/.ipc)  \n",
    "**Target:** Snowflake + dbt + datavault4dbt v1.17.0  \n",
    "\n",
    "## Pipeline Architecture\n",
    "```\n",
    "INPUT FILES\n",
    "    │\n",
    "    ▼\n",
    "[Agent 1] Reverse Engineer   → Extracts sources, targets, transformations, mappings\n",
    "    │\n",
    "    ▼\n",
    "[Agent 2] STTM Generator     → Source-to-Target Mapping document (Excel + JSON)\n",
    "    │\n",
    "    ▼\n",
    "[Agent 3] Data Vault Modeler → Hubs, Links, Satellites, PIT tables (datavault4dbt)\n",
    "    │\n",
    "    ▼\n",
    "[Agent 4] DBT Generator      → Staging, Raw Vault, Business Vault SQL + YAML configs\n",
    "    │\n",
    "    ▼\n",
    "[Agent 5] Data Profiler      → ydata-profiling + Presidio PII classification\n",
    "    │\n",
    "    ▼\n",
    "[Agent 6] Reconciliation     → Row count, checksum, column-level recon recommendations\n",
    "    │\n",
    "    ▼\n",
    "[Agent 7] Data Quality       → Rule engine: nulls, types, referential integrity, patterns\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "## References\n",
    "- [datavault4dbt](https://github.com/ScalefreeCOM/datavault4dbt) v1.17.0\n",
    "- [turbovault4dbt](https://github.com/ScalefreeCOM/turbovault4dbt)\n",
    "- [Data Vault 2.0 on Databricks/Snowflake patterns](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/blog/analyticsazure/data-vault-2-0-using-databricks-lakehouse-architecture-on-azure/3797493)"
   ]
  },
